    "body": "#### Software and hardware versions \r\nCollect v1.14.x, Android v 4.1, 4.2, 4.4, 5.1, 6.0 and 7.0.x.x, device used...\r\n\r\n#### Problem description\r\nOpenStreetMap reset on geo widgets when rotate screen when it should just change an orientation to horizontal.\r\nGif of the issue:\r\n[4-20-18-12-40-PM.mp4.zip](https://github.com/opendatakit/collect/files/1931907/4-20-18-12-40-PM.mp4.zip)\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the problem\r\n1. Choose OpenStreeMap as mapping sdk (General Settings/ User Interface/ Mapping)\r\n2. Go to Geopoint widget (geopoint type with placement-map appearance/geopoint type with maps appearance/geotrace type with no appearance/geoshape type with no appearance)\r\n3. Start loading loction\r\n4. Zoom to current location\r\n5. Rotate screen.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nMap shouldn't disappear it should just rotate - the same as when Google Maps is chosen as mapping sdk.\r\n\r\n#### Other information \r\n- this issue doesn't occur on Android 8.1\r\n- this issue concerns only geotrace type with no appearance and geoshape type with no appearance widgets on Android 6. \r\n- I used a regular All wigdets.xml form.\r\n",
